<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4093> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4093" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Assuming illegal command of the army of Valerius Flaccus, he defeated the forces of Mithridates' son at Miletopolis and penned in Mithridates himself at Pitane, in addition to sacking Cyzicus and Ilium (FGrH 2 B. 115 1, no. 252; Diod. 38. 8; Liv. Per. 83, and fr. 20 in Augustin. CD 3.7; Vell. 2.24.1; Strabo 13.1.27, 594c; Frontin. Str. 3.17.5; Plut. Sull. 23.6; Luc. 3.4-8; App. Mith. 52-53, and 56; Gran. Lic. 33 B; Memnon 34, in FGrH 3 B.353, and 40, ibid. 356; Dio 30-35, fr. 104.6-7; Obseq. 56b; Auct. Fir. Ill. 70.2-4; Oros. 6.2.9-11). When his army was taken over by Sulla at Thyatira he committed suicide in the Asclepicium at Pergamum (FGrH 2B.1151, no. 252; Diod. 38.8; Liv. Per. 83; Vell. 2.24.1; Strabo 13.1.27, 594c; Plut. Sull. 25.1; App. Mith. 59-60; Auct. Fir. Ill. 70.4; Oros. 62.9-11)." ;
	dprr:hasID 4093 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4076> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4076" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Legate of the Consul Valerius Flaccus, whom he killed in a mutiny. He seized command of Valerius' army (Diod. 38.8.1-2; Liv. Per. 82; Strabo 13.1.27, 594c; Vell. 2.24.1; Plut. Sull. 23.6; Luc. 7.2; Memnon in FGrH" ;
	dprr:hasID 4076 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4030> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4030" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent by Marius and Cinna to the Samnites to concede terms which h«d been refused by Metellus and the Senate, and won their support for the Marians (Gran. Lic. 29B; cf. Liv. Per. 80; App. BC 1.68)." ;
	dprr:hasID 4030 .
